Cannabis plants with an estimated street value of more than Â£500,000 have been seized from an address in Telford.Police searched a house on Holyhead Road in Oakengates on Tuesday morning and discovered more than 400 plants.A 22-year-old man was arrested at the property on suspicion of the production of cannabis.Two others, a man aged 45, and a woman aged 46, were arrested at a second address also on suspicion of the production of cannabis, West Mercia Police said.
All three remain in police custody as inquiries continue.
